INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5892","letter","1814-06-02","London","","ENG","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","Since Mr. Bayard's and my joint letter of 23d ult., announcing to you that the negotiations for peace would take place at Ghent, Mr. Bayard has proceeded to that city by way of Paris.","ltr_alg5892.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5893","letter","1814-06-03","London","","ENG","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","I had in April last written to Mr. Crawford urging the necessity of obtaining the friendly offices of the Emperor of Russia.","ltr_alg5893.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5894","letter","1814-06-13","London","","ENG","Albert","Gallatin","","Henry","Clay","","individual","","The armament fitted against America will enable the British, besides providing for Canada, to land at least 15 to 20,000 men on the Atlantic coast.","ltr_alg5894.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5896","letter","1814-06-20","London","","ENG","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","I received a letter from Mr. Clay, dated at Gottenburg the 1st, and informing me that he would leave it on the next day and proceed by land to Ghent","ltr_alg5896.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5897","letter","1814-06-26","Ghent","","BEL","Albert","Gallatin","","R","Beasley","","individual","","Mr. Adams writes to you for the purpose of obtaining for the John Adams a passport similar in form to that granted for the Neptune","ltr_alg5897.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5898","letter","1814-08-20","Ghent","","BEL","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","The British will naturally attempt the conquest of what they wish to acquire by the peace. They will make great efforts in Canada with respect to the possession of Lakes Ontario and Erie, for the recapture of Detroi","ltr_alg5898.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5899","letter","1814-10-26","Ghent","","BEL","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","The only advantage arising from it is that a change in Europe or a reverse of the British in America might alter their views and produce a peace - that whilst we continue here it may be made at any time","ltr_alg5899.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5900","letter","1814-12-24","Ghent","","BEL","Albert","Gallatin","","","secratary of the treasury","position","individual","","Our bankers at Amsterdam informed me at the beginning of November that no remittances for the payment of the dividend due 1st January next at Amsterdam on the Louisiana stock had yet reached them.","ltr_alg5900.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5901","letter","1814-12-25","Ghent","","BEL","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","The treaty of peace we signed yesterday with the British ministers is, in my opinion, as favorable as could be expected under existing circumstances, so far as they were known to us.","ltr_alg5901.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5902","letter","1815-09-04","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Madison","","individual","","I have sent by Mr. Cutts the convention for regulating the commercial intercourse with Great Britain, and will write on that subject to the Secretary of State.","ltr_alg5902.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5903","letter","1815-09-06","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Thomas","Jefferson","","individual","","France, which alone can have a navy, will, under her present dynasty, be for some years a vassal of her great rival","ltr_alg5903.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5904","letter","1815-09-24","Greenwich","","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Richard","Bache","","individual","","But I cannot serve them in the station with which they would honor me. My property is not half sufficient to support me anywhere but in the Western country.","ltr_alg5904.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090823142222,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5905","letter","1815-09-25","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","A","Dallas","","individual","","The specie or silver ruble contains 282 troy grains of pure silver, and is worth about 76 cents money of the United States.","ltr_alg5905.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5906","letter","1815-11-06","Washington","MD","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Blake","","individual","","I request you to return my thanks to the corporation of the city of Washington for the favorable opinion they entertain of the manner in which the duties enjoined on the ministers employed in negotiating peace with Great Britain","ltr_alg5906.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5907","letter","1815-11-23","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Madison","","individual","","I have ultimately decided not to go to France, and write this day accordingly to the Secretary of State.","ltr_alg5907.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5908","letter","1815-11-23","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","I find it necessary to decline accepting the appointment of minister of the United States to the Court of France, which the President had been pleased to bestow on me.","ltr_alg5908.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5909","letter","1815-11-23","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Henry","Clay","","individual","","You must have received a letter from the Treasury similar to that written to me respecting duties on our baggage. I have not answered mine, wishing first to know what you intend to do.","ltr_alg5909.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5910","letter","1815-11-25","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","Whilst last at Washington I communicated some observations connected with the late commercial convention with Great Britain, which, in conformity with your suggestion, I will now reduce to writing.","ltr_alg5910.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5911","letter","1815-11-27","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Thomas","Jefferson","","individual","","Our opinion of Bonaparte is precisely the same. In that La Fayette's and every friend of rational liberty in France did coincide. The return of that man was generally considered by them as a curse.","ltr_alg5911.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5912","letter","1815-11-30","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","I have the honor to enclose a copy of the inofficial note presented to the Emperor of Russia on the 19th of June, 1814, and alluded to in my letter to you of 21st of same month.","ltr_alg5912.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5913","letter","1815-12-04","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Josiah","Meigs","","individual","","I mean a most unfounded and wicked charge, that I had speculated or was in some shape connected with purchases or speculations of the public lands of the United States.","ltr_alg5913.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5914","letter","1815-12-12","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","A","Dallas","","individual","","The order to cause the ship American Eagle to be seized and libelled having been transmitted by the Secretary of the Treasury whilst I held the office, Mr. Gelston has repeatedly called on me on that subject","ltr_alg5914.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5915","letter","1815-12-26","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","I can assure you that I feel a great reluctance to part with ray personal and political friends, and that every consideration merely personal to myself and detached from my family urges a continuance in public life.","ltr_alg5915.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5916","letter","1816-01-04","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Henry","Clay","","individual","","On 7th of June we delivered to the British plenipotentiaries our project of treaty, containing, as part of the 2d Article","ltr_alg5916.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5917","letter","1816-01-31","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","John","Forsyth","","individual","","I do not know whether the debates of Congress on the bill for carrying into effect the convention with Great Britain have been correctly reported.","ltr_alg5917.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5918","letter","1816-02-02","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","I have received your letter of 27th ult., and have at last concluded to avail myself of the permission given me to accept again the mission to France. I am duly sensible of yours and the President's kindness","ltr_alg5918.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5919","letter","1816-03-19","Washington","MD","US","Albert","Gallatin","","T","Gold","","individual","","The information you have received that I was concerned with Mr. Astor in the importing business is altogether erroneous.","ltr_alg5919.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5920","letter","1816-04-01","Washington","MD","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Thomas","Jefferson","","individual","","After what I had written to you, you could hardly have expected that I would have accepted the French mission.","ltr_alg5920.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5921","letter","1816-04-18","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Madison","","individual","","Your letter of the 12th reached me only the day before yesterday, and, not willing to make a hasty decision, I have delayed an answer till to-day.","ltr_alg5921.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5922","letter","1816-04-18","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","Whether I go in a public or private vessel, it will cost me about 2000 dollars before I can land my family at Paris.","ltr_alg5922.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5923","letter","1816-04-19","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Madison","","individual","","In April, 1813, when the Federalists of New York refused to subscribe to the 16 millions loan, he came out with a subscription of more than two millions of dollars","ltr_alg5923.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5924","letter","1816-04-23","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Nathaniel","Macon","","individual","","The sale of United States stock will undoubtedly assist not only the banks but also their debtors.","ltr_alg5924.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5925","letter","1816-05-07","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Matthew","Lyon","","individual","","The war has been productive of evil and good, but I think the good preponderates. Independent of the loss of lives, and of the losses in property by individuals, the war has laid the foundation of permanent taxes and military establishment","ltr_alg5925.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5926","letter","1816-05-15","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Monroe","","individual","","I perceive that in the printed correspondence of the American ministers at Ghent my name is omitted in the despatch of 12th August, 1814, to the Secretary of State.","ltr_alg5926.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5927","letter","1816-06-02","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Madison","","individual","","I duly received your letter, and will of course see La Fayette and procure the busts.","ltr_alg5927.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5928","letter","1816-06-04","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Madison","","individual","","During the twelve years I was in the Treasury I procured places only for two friends.","ltr_alg5928.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5929","letter","1816-06-07","New York","NY","US","Albert","Gallatin","","James","Madison","","individual","","I am urging the captain of the Peacock, and still hope that he will be ready to sail the day after to-morrow.","ltr_alg5929.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_alg5930","letter","1807-12-02","Treasury Department","MD","US","Albert","Gallatin","","Thomas","Jefferson","","individual","","Supposing that the power to lay embargoes should be considered as improper to be vested in the President during the session of Congress, how would this plan answer ?","ltr_alg5930.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,42,0);
